<section class="content-section">
  <h2>2. Google Search Console</h2>
  <p>
    We use Google Search Console to understand how people find us through search engines. 
    This is a webmaster tool, not user tracking. It shows us:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Which search queries lead to our site</li>
    <li>How our pages appear in search results</li>
    <li>Technical issues with our site</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <strong>Important:</strong> Google Search Console does NOT track individual users, 
    does NOT use cookies, and does NOT collect personal data. It only shows aggregate 
    search statistics.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="content-section">
